{
  "stem": "24614.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's in France like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's in Belgium like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's Holland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother said, OK, for a few hours, you can go to the Belgielei with him, Kaiserlei.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, can show him the opera and this and that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I went with Danny.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I really went with him and showed him all of the underworld.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we walked the streets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had an awful lot in common.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, whatever subject he brought up, I had too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had a little less knowledge because I didn't have knowledge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I was in hiding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What he saw from us-- he kept on telling me about America.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I shouldn't think America is a rich country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's rich for certain people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He told me about his parents, how poor they are and how the drugstore barely they can live on it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he lives in a neighborhood, he said, not like-- I showed him my neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's not the neighborhood he lives in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he used to tell me all the reality of America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he used to speak a lot about this father and mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now he was an only child, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Yeah, and then I took him to a cafe, a very beautiful cafe right in the heart of Antwerp, where the violinist plays beautiful music and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I told the violinist what I want him to play for me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I'll never forget that song, 'Solveig's Song,' Grieg's 'Solveig's Song.' I don't know if you know it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It says, the winter [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The seasons can go and come, but your love will always stay with me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's a very beautiful Grieg song.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Edvard Grieg wrote it in German.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
